<br>
Why make a distinction between alts and mains? That's all I want to know.<br>
<br>
I know for a fact that the end-game guilds are not interested in Nagafen or Vox, but if they want to sign up their alts for a bit of low-end epic-bashing, I have no problem with that.<br>
<br>
Personally I didn't see any great problems with the old system (other than the list length), but I'll gladly accept that Twiggie was watching the list carefully, and could see some ways to improve matters. No argument here.<br>
<br>
I don't think I ever said anything approaching <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;We love having alts get loot. As long as it isn't yours, cause you got too much stuff. If its ours its ok. We just want a system that lets us get loot&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Now if others have (over the course of several posts here), fair enough, but that's certainly not my position.<br>
<br>
Let me rephrase the question: with enough 'secret squirrel' alts running round the server claiming rolls on loot that casual mains would love, what is the point in making a requirement for the characters to be primaries? It seems to me it just penalises the honest people who declare that their alts are such, and encourages people to hide their rep behind their alts' names. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucamala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/7/02 4:21:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Vox/Nagafen rules posted and effective immediately.</span><hr size=1> IMO the &quot;small guy&quot; is not someone of low lvl, its someone who is not in a large guild. if you have a high lvl in a guild that is not able to kill kunark dragons your best chance to ever killl a dragon is naggy/vox with your alt. <br>
<br>
I'm pretty sure no one would &quot;monopolize&quot; naggy or vox if they was ffa, thats not really an argument here.<br>
<br>
biggest problem of trak rotation (and why we don't have official new rotations) seems to be that people who couldn't kill something in an ffa environment could do it with the rotation. now we're doing the opposite thing: people who could kill naggy/vox with ffa are not allowed to get on the list. i don't think this is the right way to go.<br>
