<br>
I trust Twiggie.  While I don't always agree with his actions/changes, I believe he has more sense and experience in the matter and that changes are for the best.  It's good that there are agruments made from the changes, it means that people are checking the actions of each other and making compromises.  If there were no one to contest the changes, then no compromise would be made and even may lead to abuse of the system.  Checks and balances.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think everyone should have a chance at leading their own dragon raid; I too wish to lead one, as I find being a leader to be rewarding.  Yes, there are people who will maliciously abuse the system, but that is why these things are discussed:  To make sure no one is being punished more severly than the abuser.  It is disappointing to see that people are limited to what raids they can lead because of your guildstatus/level, but they should not turn their anger towards Twiggie for that change -- It is the ones who abused it who is to blame.<br>
<br>
While I would like to lead a Dragon raid, I fear that I may outlevel the restriction by the time my date comes up.  It is pitiful that it takes so long to realize what you would like to do later in levels.  Some people may have found this realization and too saw it too late -- They put their hopes in their alternate characters who could do what they could not because of their level.  <br>
<br>
Even when I reach 60, I hope to lead a Nagafen/Vox raid with an alternate character, and not be prevented from doing so because of my guildstatus and the level of my main character.  When that time comes, I hope that the changes won't be as significant as to prevent me from doing so.<br>
<br>
Hrm, I hope that wasn't too long.  Again, this is my view and opinion of the situation, not a question of the rules or such.<br>
<br>
Edit:  Just to point out, I will probably be leading it as an independant.  I am not or have ever been guilded.<br>
